cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SI

The paper proposes a regularization formulation for multi-task learning, which is a common topic in machine learning. The paper discusses the relationships between tasks and identifies outlier tasks, which suggests a focus on learning the structure of the data. This makes categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) likely candidates. Among these, cs.LG is the most likely category as it is the primary subfield of machine learning and the paper focuses on improving generalization performance. cs.AI is also a likely category as the paper discusses learning relationships between tasks, which is a common topic in AI research. cs.CV and cs.CL are also possible categories as they deal with structured data and natural language processing, respectively. Finally, cs.SI is a less likely category as it focuses on social networks and information systems, which are not directly related to the topic of the paper.
